Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a medium #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice half the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) (whole onion for 4 servings). Finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). Trim @zucchini{1}(grated on the largest holes of a box grater), then grate on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until almost al dente, ~{8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 6).

Drain penne. (Keep empty #pot handy for step 5.)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add diced onion, tomato, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @marinara sauce{14%oz}, zucchini, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), @water{1/4%cup} (1/2 cup for 4), @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), and a big pinch of salt. (You'll use more Italian Seasoning in the next step.) Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring, ~{3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

> Use pan used for beef or sausage here. Once sauce is done, return turkey or sausage to pan; stir to combine.

While sauce simmers, in a medium #bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%oz}, @Italian seasoning{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings), and a drizzle of olive oil. (Use the rest of the Italian Seasoning as you like.) Season with salt and pepper.

Add drained penne, sauce, and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to #pot used for pasta. Season with salt and pepper; stir to thoroughly combine.

Spread out half the pasta mixture in an 8-by-8-inch #baking dish{}. (For 4, use a 9-by-13-inch baking dish.) Using a #tablespoon{}, dollop pasta mixture with herbed ricotta. Top with remaining pasta mixture, then sprinkle with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

Cover baking dish with #foil{}. (TIP: Coat inside of foil with nonstick spray first to prevent sticking.) Bake pasta on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from oven; discard foil.

Heat broiler to high. Broil until cheese is lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let cool slightly; top with @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Divide between plates and serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.